WEBVTT

00:02.436 --> 00:03.468
[ Remote clicks ]

00:03.503 --> 00:05.037
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.574 --> 00:10.442
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.745
♪ I'm gonna do what I want
all day! ♪

00:13.780 --> 00:16.381
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:16.416 --> 00:18.316
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:18.351 --> 00:22.755
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:25.058 --> 00:29.061
[ "Hail to the Chief" plays ]

00:29.096 --> 00:30.429
When you think about it,

00:30.464 --> 00:33.031
these are the branches
of the government, okay?

00:33.066 --> 00:36.201
On our, um,
big constitutional tree.

00:36.236 --> 00:37.702
Oh, which reminds me...
[ Bell rings ]

00:37.737 --> 00:38.770
[ Kids cheer ]

00:38.805 --> 00:40.906
Okay, wait!
Before you go to lunch --

00:40.941 --> 00:43.542
Ow! Darn it! --
I just want to remind everyone

00:43.577 --> 00:45.677
that we are elections
for class president this week.

00:45.712 --> 00:47.546
The sign up sheet
is over by the door.

00:47.581 --> 00:49.514
The election is open
so anyone can...

00:49.549 --> 00:50.882
and no one cares.
[ Wooden thud ]

00:50.917 --> 00:53.585
Uh, Jeff.

00:53.620 --> 00:55.120
Jeff?

00:55.155 --> 00:57.722
Jeff? [ Echoes ]

00:57.757 --> 00:59.257
Jeff. [ Echoes ]

00:59.292 --> 01:00.559
Jeff!
- Huh?

01:00.594 --> 01:02.260
[ Microphone feedback ]
Your rebuttal?

01:02.295 --> 01:04.596
Um, uh.

01:04.631 --> 01:06.431
Uh, um.

01:06.466 --> 01:10.402
W-Well,
my stance on that,

01:10.437 --> 01:12.070
uh...

01:12.105 --> 01:14.406
[ Microphone feedback ]

01:14.441 --> 01:16.241
Ms. Baker!
- Aah! Oh! Jeff!

01:16.276 --> 01:17.809
I -- Jeff, hi.
You're still here.

01:17.844 --> 01:20.879
Ms. Baker,
- will the election this year

01:20.914 --> 01:22.414
be based on merit or...?

01:22.449 --> 01:23.949
It's based on student votes,
Jeff.

01:23.984 --> 01:25.818
Just like last year.

01:28.755 --> 01:30.155
[ Sighs ]

01:30.190 --> 01:32.057
Hey, Jeff, here.

01:32.092 --> 01:33.792
Vote for me or whatever.

01:33.827 --> 01:34.926
Oh, Belson, are you...

01:34.961 --> 01:38.163
Why are you handing out
gray circles?

01:38.198 --> 01:40.765
Having a class president
is totally pointless.

01:40.800 --> 01:43.135
So, vote for me and everything
will stay the same.

01:43.170 --> 01:48.340
Or don't,
I don't care.

01:48.375 --> 01:51.176
[ Distant sobbing,
sniffling ]

01:57.484 --> 01:59.284
Good job, Amy!

01:59.319 --> 02:01.953
[ Sobbing continues,
yells ]

02:01.988 --> 02:04.156
All right, he gets it.

02:04.191 --> 02:07.659
[ Indistinct chattering ]

02:09.629 --> 02:11.796
Yeah. Yogurt.
Sure. Yep.

02:11.831 --> 02:13.798
Eat it!
Okay. Down the hatch.

02:13.833 --> 02:17.636
[ Gulping ]
[ Excited chatter ]

02:17.671 --> 02:21.273
Hmm. Clarence
is quite the crowd pleaser.

02:21.308 --> 02:23.475
He sure is!

02:23.510 --> 02:25.610
Boy: Oh, my goodness. I had no
idea a person could do that!

02:25.645 --> 02:27.345
Clarence,
- I'm gonna level with you...

02:27.380 --> 02:29.548
Oh, hey, Jeff.
[ Belches ]

02:29.583 --> 02:31.449
...the competition
will be fierce,

02:31.484 --> 02:33.151
but with me
as your manager...

02:33.186 --> 02:34.452
Do you want a milk?

02:34.487 --> 02:36.655
I traded my lunch
for everyone's milks.

02:36.690 --> 02:38.657
[ Grunts ]
No, thank you, Clarence.

02:38.692 --> 02:40.158
Look,
- with you as president...

02:40.193 --> 02:41.793
President?
What do they do again?

02:41.828 --> 02:44.329
Oh, the president
can do lots of things.

02:44.364 --> 02:46.498
Like build a castle
on the roof?

02:46.533 --> 02:50.669
Uh, yeah. Yeah, sure.
And with me as your manager --

02:50.704 --> 02:53.004
Could the president get
a math tutor for Crendle?

02:53.039 --> 02:54.406
[ Thud ]
Uh...

02:54.441 --> 02:57.008
And could a president
get a hair dresser for Amy?

02:57.043 --> 02:58.510
Oh, heck yeah.

02:58.545 --> 03:00.712
Could a president
- get a loving family for Reed?

03:00.747 --> 03:01.880
[ Quack! ]

03:01.915 --> 03:04.015
Uh, well,
some of those things.

03:04.050 --> 03:07.185
I'll do it! I'm gonna be
a man of the people!

03:07.220 --> 03:08.887
Whoo, yeah!

03:08.922 --> 03:12.023
[ Slurps, gulps ]
[ "Hail to the Chief" plays ]

03:12.058 --> 03:14.025
[ Mouse clicks ]

03:14.060 --> 03:16.228
[ Mouse clicks ]

03:16.263 --> 03:18.397
[ Lever clicks ]

03:26.640 --> 03:30.575
As president
- of Ms. Baker's classroom, 224,

03:30.610 --> 03:34.846
I'll promise to lead
with courage and di-doginity...

03:34.881 --> 03:37.549
And persevalence,
- and I'm gonna take things

03:37.584 --> 03:39.684
back to the way
they used to be.

03:39.719 --> 03:43.388
Whoo!
Clarence for president!

03:43.423 --> 03:45.924
I want to give you
a smooch.

03:45.959 --> 03:48.126
And I'm gonna put more coal
in the furnace.

03:48.161 --> 03:49.894
And a math tutor
for Crendle.

03:49.929 --> 03:52.897
Whoo!
Can I hear a Clarence?

03:52.932 --> 03:53.999
Huh? Huh?

03:56.269 --> 03:57.402
[ Gasps ] It's me!

03:57.437 --> 03:59.137
[ Wind chimes tinkle ]
Yeah.

03:59.172 --> 04:03.241
And there will be a milk
for every man, woman, and child.

04:03.276 --> 04:05.143
And no school forever!

04:05.178 --> 04:09.281
[ Cheering ]

04:09.316 --> 04:12.451
Yes.
That's how you give a speech.

04:14.020 --> 04:17.422
Hey, Emilio,
- great speech back there, huh?

04:17.457 --> 04:20.759
Well,
- I just wanted to remind you

04:20.794 --> 04:23.428
who you should be voting for
this season.

04:23.463 --> 04:25.630
Okay, love you, baby.

04:25.665 --> 04:27.999
Belson: What is this?!
He's kissing bab--

04:28.034 --> 04:30.635
He's not even a baby!
This is propaganda.

04:30.670 --> 04:33.672
I told you guys we aren't
printing about the election!

04:33.707 --> 04:36.074
Belson, we've got a tight system
going right now.

04:36.109 --> 04:37.075
So you better
get on board.

04:37.110 --> 04:38.410
[ Slurps ]

04:38.445 --> 04:39.978
Clarence is just hot right now,
I guess.

04:40.013 --> 04:44.082
[ Groans ]
Clarence is ruining everything.

04:44.117 --> 04:45.750
Wait a minute.

04:45.785 --> 04:48.787
Okay,
- for his campaign for presidency

04:48.822 --> 04:52.257
our very own Belson has prepared
a campaign ad. Huh? Fun.

04:52.292 --> 04:56.027
Here's my ad, Belson
for President, blah, blah, blah.

04:56.062 --> 04:58.663
[ As Clarence ]
<i>Oh, hello, it's me, Clarence,</i>

04:58.698 --> 05:00.699
<i>and if elected class president,</i>

05:00.734 --> 05:03.468
<i>I'll make sure there's</i>
<i>more homework for everybody.</i>

05:03.503 --> 05:04.803
[ Gasping ]

05:04.838 --> 05:07.472
[ Gasps ]
<i>And I'll reduce recess time.</i>

05:07.507 --> 05:12.711
[ Gasps ] <i>And no more bathroom breaks
and Saturday school every weekend.</i>

05:12.746 --> 05:15.180
I love you.
- Okay. Thank you, Belson.

05:15.215 --> 05:16.981
A little
mean spirited but --

05:17.016 --> 05:19.050
but good
extra curricular effort.

05:19.085 --> 05:20.118
So that's, yeah.

05:20.153 --> 05:22.387
I can't believe
I said all that stuff.

05:22.422 --> 05:25.623
That wasn't you Clarence.
That was an attack ad by Belson.

05:25.658 --> 05:27.659
And we need to attack back.
- Jeff,

05:27.694 --> 05:30.695
Belson would never do that.
But he did do it.

05:30.730 --> 05:33.398
And we got to start thinking
of ways to attack back.

05:33.433 --> 05:34.866
You got any dirt on him?
Dirt?!

05:34.901 --> 05:38.303
This campaign was built
on a foundation of promises,

05:38.338 --> 05:39.671
not dirt!

05:39.706 --> 05:42.574
You need some dirt to create
a proper foundation.

05:42.609 --> 05:44.476
Not those
worthless promises.

05:44.511 --> 05:45.577
Worthless?

05:45.612 --> 05:47.712
What about the castle
in the cloud?

05:47.747 --> 05:49.848
Forget about the castle, Clarence.
- No!

05:49.883 --> 05:52.584
This is about winning
at any cost.

05:52.619 --> 05:55.186
Even if it means
getting our hands dirty.

05:55.221 --> 05:56.554
No!

05:56.589 --> 05:58.056
[ Thud ] - Now look
at what you've done!

05:58.091 --> 06:01.059
[ Grunts ]
- Jeff, you're fired!

06:01.094 --> 06:05.330
What?! You can't fire me!
You're nothing without me!

06:05.365 --> 06:07.899
I'll see how far you go,
Clarence.

06:07.934 --> 06:09.834
Have fun!
What are you gonna do?

06:09.869 --> 06:11.870
Talk about milk some more?

06:11.905 --> 06:14.205
[ Grunts ]

06:14.240 --> 06:15.373
[ Panting ]

06:15.408 --> 06:17.909
Well, well,
look who it is.

06:17.944 --> 06:19.544
Come to make
more fake promises?

06:19.579 --> 06:21.713
[ Screams ]

06:21.748 --> 06:25.350
[ Laughs ] Want to see
what I think of Clarence?

06:25.385 --> 06:26.451
[ Grunts ]
- Yeah.

06:26.486 --> 06:29.354
I'll show you
more homework.

06:29.389 --> 06:30.955
[ Dramatic music playing ]

06:30.990 --> 06:32.090
[ Screams ]

06:32.125 --> 06:34.225
[ Pants ]

06:34.260 --> 06:37.562
[ Yells ]
[ Screeching ]

06:37.597 --> 06:42.434
[ Wind whistles ]

06:42.469 --> 06:45.570
Huh?

06:45.605 --> 06:48.940
[ "Hail to the Chief" plays ]

06:51.244 --> 06:52.978
Hmm...

06:56.416 --> 06:58.583
Hmph.

07:00.286 --> 07:02.720
[ Indistinct chatter ]

07:02.755 --> 07:04.556
Can you believe
Clarence dropped Jeff?

07:04.591 --> 07:06.391
He's flying solo now.

07:06.426 --> 07:09.093
[ Makes monkey noises ]

07:09.128 --> 07:10.929
Don't get me wrong,
he's a good friend,

07:10.964 --> 07:13.832
but I knew he didn't
have the grit to show up.

07:21.474 --> 07:22.774
[ Cellphone beeping ]

07:22.809 --> 07:24.976
Oh, uh, mm,
welcome everyone

07:25.011 --> 07:28.613
to Aberdale's 27th
annual class president election!

07:28.648 --> 07:31.316
Yay!
Uh, thank you.

07:31.351 --> 07:34.152
[ Clears throat ]
Now, let's have a few words

07:34.187 --> 07:37.288
from our first candidate,
Belson Noles! Belson?

07:37.323 --> 07:38.356
[ Clears throat ]

07:38.391 --> 07:39.757
Thank you, Ms. Baker.

07:39.792 --> 07:41.526
I'm happy to be with you all
tonight.

07:41.561 --> 07:44.929
Because this whole election
is a vessel for misery.

07:44.964 --> 07:47.699
If you vote for me,
nothing will change.

07:47.734 --> 07:50.602
Because the system
is meaningless.

07:50.637 --> 07:53.004
So vote for me, or don't.

07:53.039 --> 07:54.305
I don't care.

07:54.340 --> 07:55.440
Thank you.

07:55.475 --> 07:58.309
[ Laughs ]
Belson's tight!

07:58.344 --> 08:01.312
[ Cheers and applause ]

08:01.347 --> 08:04.849
Uh, and now for
our second candidate, Clarence!

08:04.884 --> 08:06.484
Clarence, your rebuttal?

08:06.519 --> 08:08.587
Oh, this'll be good.

08:10.590 --> 08:14.158
[ Sighs ]

08:14.193 --> 08:15.493
[ Clears throat ]

08:15.528 --> 08:19.731
[ Singing off-key ]
♪ Oh, say can you see ♪

08:19.766 --> 08:23.468
♪ By the dawn's early light ♪

08:23.503 --> 08:27.705
♪ What so proudly we saw ♪

08:27.740 --> 08:31.743
♪ [Mumbles] night ♪

08:31.778 --> 08:35.480
♪ And the rocket's red glare ♪

08:35.515 --> 08:43.088
♪ By the dawns of the brave ♪

08:44.891 --> 08:47.492
Um, okay.
Thank you, Clarence.

08:47.527 --> 08:50.028
[ Thunderous cheering ]

08:50.063 --> 08:52.063
He's just pandering
to nationalism!

08:52.098 --> 08:54.866
You're all blinded
by national pride!

08:54.901 --> 08:57.368
[ "Hail to the Chief" plays ]
Meh.

08:57.403 --> 09:02.040
[ Clarence laughs ]

09:02.075 --> 09:03.308
[ Grunts ]

09:06.079 --> 09:08.246
Clarence,
- as the new class president,

09:08.281 --> 09:10.548
you'll lead us
- in the morning announcements.

09:10.583 --> 09:13.184
Ms. Baker,
please take a seat.

09:13.219 --> 09:15.286
No, Clarence, I'm the teacher,
you can't tell me what to do.

09:15.321 --> 09:17.055
Just because you're
the president -- Shh!

09:17.090 --> 09:19.357
Ms. Baker, you've done
enough teaching today.

09:19.392 --> 09:21.225
Please join
the rest of the class.

09:21.260 --> 09:24.028
[ Sighs ] All right, well,
that's not...

09:24.063 --> 09:26.364
[ Clears throat ]
Ladies and gentlemen,

09:26.399 --> 09:29.267
as my first act
as class president,

09:29.302 --> 09:31.269
I renounce my presidency.

09:31.304 --> 09:32.637
[ All gasp ]

09:32.672 --> 09:35.640
Yeah,
- finally someone gets it!

09:35.675 --> 09:39.043
It's silly for me to carry out all
those worthless promises. Hmm?

09:39.078 --> 09:42.246
Because I can't do all of that
by myself.

09:42.281 --> 09:47.118
But as a group, as a strong
powerful team, we know --

09:47.153 --> 09:50.788
we know deep down, we can
accomplish something amazing!

09:50.823 --> 09:52.056
What are you talking about,
man?

09:52.091 --> 09:53.791
So let's all band together

09:53.826 --> 09:55.493
and build a castle
on the roof!

09:55.528 --> 09:58.596
[ Cheering ] [ Eagle screeches,
rock music playing ]

09:58.631 --> 10:00.164
♪ Yeah! ♪

10:00.199 --> 10:03.267
♪ Whoo! ♪

10:03.302 --> 10:05.903
♪ Come on! ♪

10:05.938 --> 10:09.941
You want to put another zero,
like this.

10:09.976 --> 10:12.176
Nice and round.

10:12.211 --> 10:14.412
Isn't math fun?

10:14.447 --> 10:18.182
I'm as beautiful on the outside
as I am on the inside.

10:18.217 --> 10:21.919
[ Laughs ] We're your family
now, Reed!

10:21.954 --> 10:24.689
Who wants a hug?
[ Quack! ]

10:24.724 --> 10:25.957
[ All groan ]

10:25.992 --> 10:27.458
Girl: Okay.
Boy: Ow. Thank you.

10:27.493 --> 10:29.293
Smells like cheese.

10:29.328 --> 10:31.295
Hey, Clarence?

10:31.330 --> 10:33.798
I just came by
- because I wanted to apologize

10:33.833 --> 10:35.033
for the way I was acting.

10:35.068 --> 10:37.268
It's okay, Jeff.
Look, it's the sash.

10:37.303 --> 10:40.038
I have it in my secret pocket,
right here.

10:40.073 --> 10:43.141
Here.
- Yeah, I'm not touching that.

10:43.176 --> 10:45.176
I-I have a better idea.

10:47.013 --> 10:50.048
Who needs
- a dumb old president any way?

10:50.083 --> 10:53.651
[ Laughs ] Yeah.
Who does need one?

10:53.686 --> 10:57.689
♪ Working together
is the key to success ♪

10:57.724 --> 11:03.161
♪ We'll put our differences
aside and we will triumph ♪

11:05.131 --> 11:06.898
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:08.501 --> 11:10.568
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:12.105 --> 11:13.938
♪ Picking my nose ♪
